TASK 5 - CONTINUE YOUR LEARNING: INTRO TO LAN
LAN (Local Area Network)
• A network that connects devices within a limited geographical area.
• Examples: Home network, School network, Office network.
• Devices communicate using switches, routers, and network cables/Wi-Fi.
KEY FEATURES
• High speed communication.
• Privately owned and managed.
• Used for sharing files, printers, Internet access, and resources.
EXAMPLES OF DEVICES IN A LAN
• Computers
• Laptops
• Smartphones
• Printers
• Servers
• Routers
• Switches
WHY IMPORTANT IN CYBER SECURITY?
• Most attacks begin inside or target a LAN.
• Understanding LANs helps in network scanning, enumeration, traffic analysis, and defense.
